* What is Pod?
A Pod is the smallest deployable object in Kubernetes.

Think of it as:
Pod
|--Container 1
|--Container 2
|-- Shared Network & Storage

** Pod Characteristics **
Every Pod has:
1. Own IP Address
2. Shared Storage (Conatiners inside a Pod can share volume)
3. Shared Network Namespace (Container inside the same Pod communicate using localhost)


#### Scenario 1: Create First Pod

create YAML:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# vim nginx.yml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: nginx-pod
spec:
  containers:
    - name: nginx
      image: nginx:latest

Deploy:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl apply -f nginx.yml

Verify:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl get pods
NAME        READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE
nginx-pod   1/1     Running   0          25s

Inspect Pod:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl describe pod nginx-pod


#### Pod Lifecycle
pending
   ↓
ContainerCreationg
   ↓
Running
   ↓
Succeeded
   ↓
Failed

Check:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl get pods -w

Accessing Pod:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl exec -it nginx-pod -- bash

Delete Pod:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl delete pod nginx-pod


####### Scenario 2: Create a log-generating pod
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# busybox.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod

metadata:
  name: logger

spec:
  containers:
  - name: logger
    image: busybox
    command:
      - /bin/sh
      - -c
      - while true; do date; sleep 5; done

[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl apply -f busybox.yaml

View Logs:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl logs logger

Follow logs:
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl logs -f logger



####### Scenario 3: ImagePullBackOff
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# vim badimage.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod

metadata:
  name: badimage

spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:abc123

[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl apply -f badimage.yaml
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl get pods
NAME        READY   STATUS             RESTARTS     AGE
nginx   0/1     ImagePullBackOff   1 (7s ago)   13s

:::::Troubleshooting::::
[root@k8s-control01 ~]# kubectl describe pod badimage

Observe:
Failed to pull image

Fix:
image: nginx:latest



